# Context Engine & Universal Calendar Layer

See [CONTEXT_ENGINE.md](../../CONTEXT_ENGINE.md).

## Rules

1. Aipify is the intelligence layer **above** calendars — never a replacement calendar app.
2. Business logic in Supabase RPCs; API routes and panels are thin clients.
3. OAuth providers connect as `pending` until authorization completes — never fake sync.
4. `aipify_internal` calendar is auto-provisioned; cannot be disconnected.
5. Natural language scheduling requires user confirmation before `create_calendar_event`.
6. Context pulls from PAME, LifeOS, RSI, Identity — separate concerns, unified display.
7. Platform `/platform/trust` uses `get_platform_context_overview` — aggregates only.
8. i18n: `customerApp.contextEngine.*`, `customerApp.universalCalendar.*`, `platform.contextEngine.*` in en/no/sv/da.

## Tables

`context_settings` · `calendar_connections` · `calendar_events` · `calendar_sync_log`

## Routes

`/app/assistant/context` · `/app/assistant/calendars`
